commits.commitMessage:
Add IP handling to Wi-Fi Access Point sample Application 'wifiWebAPPt'

The WiFi AP is a 3G gateway and can now be configured,
started and stopped through a web page.
The configuration concerns:
 - the SSID,
 - the WiFi channel,
 - the number of stations,
 - the security (WPA, passphrase/PSK, visibility...)
 - the IP adresses range (with check of the input)
Logs are available as well in order to know the AP status.
It includes a correction concerning the shutdown of the hostapd daemon.
WARNING: The last line with the conf-file option in the dnsmasq.conf
configuration file has to be removed. Otherwise, the dnsmasq daemon will
not start properly and as a result, the AP will not work.

Change-Id: I74e9a3b53f7c802198c02acd4d50c1565dc35366

commits.commitMessage:
trac:4197 - [WiFi] Add "make docs".... This is the framework that connects the make docs with the mangOH projects doxygen main page in the doc/external_mainpage.dox Patch B.2: - updated wifi command line tool doxygen help Patch B.1: - new commit since old is on master. - Fixed compile warning with gcc when running make docs. because the make docs is not yet on legato it has not been seen (yet) - removed API genearation warning. - ! Noticed a problem with 'make docs' and GPIOExpander. Gcc is lacking a headerfile. Please see #4566 for that. Btw this is how it is all connected: This enables Legato to build doxygen and include a link to a mainpage from another project. The other system must define the following export EXTERNAL_DOXYGEN_DEFINE = EXTERNAL_DOXYGEN_DEFINE export EXTERNAL_DOXYGEN_ROOT = $(PROJECTX_ROOT)/apps/WiFi and it must also have a doxygen page called "external_proj_mainpage" These defines are defined in targetDefs.projectx and will be read by CMake. framework/doc/Cmakelist.txt: EXTERNAL_DOXYGEN_DEFINE EXTERNAL_DOXYGEN_ROOT and sets CMAKE_EXTERNAL_DOXYGEN_ROOT They are then transfered into the soon to be preproccessed doxygen config files : framework/doc/doxygen.implementation.cfg.in framework/doc/doxygen.user.cfg.in These doxygen configuration files are preprocessed by CMake and enables basic variable expansion. Please note that doxygen variables are very restrictive and only the ones set with the variable ENABLED_SECTIONS in the config file are available. This all enables the usage of conditional (similare to ifdef) usage to include/exclude text.
